HEADWORD: Dentiphone
<hw>Den"ti*phone</hw> <pr>(d⟦ecr⟧n"t⟦icr⟧*f⟦omac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>dens</ets>, <ets>dentis</ets>, tooth + Gr.
<grk>fwnh`</grk> sound.]</ety> <def>An instrument which, placed against
the teeth, conveys sound to the auditory nerve; an audiphone.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
